      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Developer Position\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior Developer position at our Austin-based company. We were genuinely impressed by your skills in system design and your strong cultural fit during the interview process. Your enthusiasm and dedication were evident, and we appreciate the time you invested in our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. This decision was not easy, as we were very impressed with your abilities and potential. We believe that this choice will best serve our current needs and help us achieve our goals more effectively.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision does not reflect on your qualifications or potential. We have no doubt that you will find success in your future endeavors, and we wish you all the best in your career journey.\n\nThank you once again for considering us as a potential employer. We hope that our paths may cross again in the future, and we encourage you to apply for any future opportunities that align with your skills and interests.\n\nWarm regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[",
